we-stay-angry" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;janelia.org/news/fighting-frui&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;t-flies-help-researchers-understand-why-we-stay-angry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/drosophila" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;drosophila&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111494877806912200</guid><pubDate>Wed, 29 Nov 2023 16:53:38 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>nature :press:</title><link>https://press.coop/@Nature/111494725797502093</link><description>‚ÄòDisruptive‚Äô science more likely from teams who work in the same placeNature, Published online: 29 November 2023; doi:10.1038/d41586-023-03618-xAnalysis of millions of papers shows that farflung collaborators produce fewer big breakthroughs than groups working together in person. &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://press.coop/tags/press" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;press&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-023-03618-x?utm_source=press.coop" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;nature.com/articles/d41586-023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;-03618-x?utm_source=press.coop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111495169286249667</guid><pubDate>Wed, 29 Nov 2023 18:07:49 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Catherine (Katie) Schretter</title><link>https://drosophila.social/@ceschretter/111496196533597277</link><description>1/8 How do certain states, like aggression, persist? Excited to share our recent collaborative work (&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1101/2023.06.07.543722" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;doi.org/10.1101/2023.06.07.543&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;722&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) using the relatively understudied model of female fruit fly aggression to examine such questions. Thanks so much to HHMI Janelia for their story on it (&lt;a href="https://www.janelia.org/news/fighting-fruit-flies-help-researchers-understand-why-we-stay-angry" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;janelia.org/news/fighting-frui&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;t-flies-help-researchers-understand-why-we-stay-angry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)! &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://drosophila.social/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://drosophila.social/tags/drosophila" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;drosophila&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111496348060211735</guid><pubDate>Wed, 29 Nov 2023 23:07:36 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111496786934352946</link><description>It's not just rhythms.  It is transient bursts of rhythms.Transient oscillations as computations for cognition: Analysis, modeling and function&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.conb.2023.102796" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;doi.org/10.1016/j.conb.2023.10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;2796&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111496787052048283</guid><pubDate>Thu, 30 Nov 2023 00:59:12 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/111498899715498366</link><description>Oh dear, the Guardian.&lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/nov/29/the-alien-hunter-has-harvard-avi-loeb-found-proof-of-extraterrestrial-life" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;theguardian.com/science/2023/n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;ov/29/the-alien-hunter-has-harvard-avi-loeb-found-proof-of-extraterrestrial-life&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111498899715498366</guid><pubDate>Thu, 30 Nov 2023 09:56:31 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111500775497154772</link><description>Hey, that's me.&lt;br/&gt;Earl Miller on How We Think About the Brain&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://ilp.mit.edu/watch/earl-k-miller-profile" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;ilp.mit.edu/watch/earl-k-mille&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;r-profile&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111500775824135236</guid><pubDate>Thu, 30 Nov 2023 17:53:33 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Carl Zimmer</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@Carl_Zimmer/111501255772982399</link><description>Penguins fall asleep thousands of times a day, for just a few seconds. Here‚Äôs my story on nature‚Äôs extreme nappers. Gift link: &lt;a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/30/science/penguin-naps-sleep.html?unlocked_article_code=1.CU0.KS0f.KxJXtNoodUo5&amp;amp;smid=url-share " rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;nytimes.com/2023/11/30/science&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;/penguin-naps-sleep.html?unlocked_article_code=1.CU0.KS0f.KxJXtNoodUo5&amp;amp;smid=url-share &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111501255772982399</guid><pubDate>Thu, 30 Nov 2023 19:55:42 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Robin Gutzen</title><link>https://mstdn.social/@rgutzen/111501413288431764</link><description>Did you ever wish constructing a neural data analysis was more like a choose-your-own-adventure story? üë®‚ÄçüíªWe just released version 0.1. of the "Collaborative Brain Wave Analysis Pipeline (Cobrawap)" üêç&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://cobrawap.readthedocs.io" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;cobrawap.readthedocs.io&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Simply pick and combine reusable method blocks and parameter configurations to build a reproducible &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mstdn.social/tags/AnalysisWorkflow" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;AnalysisWorkflow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that is adaptable to heterogenous data sources of cortical wave activity üåäüß†&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mstdn.social/tags/Neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mstdn.social/tags/ResearchSoftware" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;ResearchSoftware&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mstdn.social/tags/BrainWaves" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;BrainWaves&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111501413364271421</guid><pubDate>Thu, 30 Nov 2023 20:35:45 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Robin Gutzen</title><link>https://mstdn.social/@rgutzen/111501417697529671</link><description>üìú There is also a preprint showcasing the application of Cobrawap for a meta-analysis across 60 open-access ECoG and calcium-imaging recordings from anesthetized mice:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2211.08527" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2211.08&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;527&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;... a peer-reviewed publication is following very soon, but the code for replicating the results/figures is already available: &lt;a href="https://gin.g-node.org/INM-6/cobrawap_publication_code" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;gin.g-node.org/INM-6/cobrawap_&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;publication_code&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111501418602173355</guid><pubDate>Thu, 30 Nov 2023 20:36:52 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Prof Christina Pagel</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@chrischirp/111501732660151066</link><description>Was interviewed on Channel 4 News tonight about Hancock's testimony... covered the toxic Downing street environment, sincerity, asymptomatic spread and Inquiry learning.&lt;a href="https://www.channel4.com/news/covid-inquiry-matt-hancock-denies-lying-during-pandemic" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;channel4.com/news/covid-inquir&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;y-matt-hancock-denies-lying-during-pandemic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111501953312344001</guid><pubDate>Thu, 30 Nov 2023 22:53:05 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Albert Cardona</title><link>https://mathstodon.xyz/@albertcardona/111502600266964122</link><description>The Devineni lab at Emory University is recruiting a research assistant and PhD students, funded by the NIH, to work on &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/Drosophila" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Drosophila&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;a href="https://devinenilab.org/join-us" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;devinenilab.org/join-us&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/Fedihire" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Fedihire&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/PhDjobs" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;PhDjobs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111502625755637512</guid><pubDate>Fri, 01 Dec 2023 01:44:06 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>David Schoppik</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@schoppik/111502811929289202</link><description>Seeing the whole "Paris is considering coexisting with rats" recirculating &lt;a href="https://www.insider.com/can-humans-and-rates-just-live-together-paris-new-york-2023-6" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;insider.com/can-humans-and-rat&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;es-just-live-together-paris-new-york-2023-6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and PEOPLE we did this and it ends deliciously.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/111/502/808/165/219/988/original/20e7f4a447ea7973.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/111/502/808/165/219/988/original/20e7f4a447ea7973.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111502811929289202</guid><pubDate>Fri, 01 Dec 2023 02:31:27 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Albert Cardona</title><link>https://mathstodon.xyz/@albertcardona/111502628793892374</link><description>Loren Looger, legendary protein wrangler, who always generously shared their genetically encoded calcium indicators and more while still in development and unpublished, is asking for labs to co-write grants with him:"Dear science world, I need help, please. If you like the tools and data we generate, and our shareware attitude, can you please co-apply for funding with us? It turns out that I'm terrible at writing grants, and we need $$ or else we can't make more GCaMPs, RCaMPs, SnFRs (we've branched out to neuromodulators and neuropeptides), FPs, viruses, tags, etc. We'll also make whatever you want, but we need $$ to do it. DM or email me, sooner is better. Sorry to be desperate, but we want to keep doing this, and I'm not sure we can."&lt;a href="https://profiles.ucsd.edu/loren.looger" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;profiles.ucsd.edu/loren.looger&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt